Definition:
State plan amendment (SPA) ID number using the following format: SS-YY-NNNN-xxxx where:
SS = State (use the two character postal abbreviation for your state);

YY = Calendar Year (last two characters of the calendar year of the state plan amendment);

NNNN = SPA number (a four character number beginning with 0001) States should track their submissions to assign sequential numbers to their submissions.

xxxx = Optional, 1 to 4 characters alpha/numeric modifier (Suffix)

States should use the specific SPA that covered the services rendered.

